dashboard.description:
Monitor your Apache JMeter load test in real time with InfluxDB and Grafana.
Get overall summary, errors details and particular transaction response times.

targets.query:
from(bucket: "mighty-meter")
|> range(start: -100y)
|> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "events" and (r._value =~ /started/ or r._value =~ /ended/) and (r._value =~ /${qtest}/ or r.application =~ /${qtest}/ or r.env =~ /${qtest}/ ))
|> keep(columns: ["_value","application","env","duration","users","version","_time"])
|> group()
 |> rename(columns: {_time: "start", _value: "event", duration: "duration (sg)"})

from(bucket: v.defaultBucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "statistics")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "count" and  r["statut"] == "ok" and r.application == "${app}" and r.env == "${env}" and r.version == "${version}" and r.test == "${test}" and r.duration == "${duration}" and r.users == "${users}")
  |> keep(columns: ["_field","_time","_value"])
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: sum)
  |> sum()

from(bucket: "mighty-meter")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "statistics")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"]  =~ /count/ and r["transaction"] == "all" and r.application == "${app}" and r.env == "${env}" and r.version == "${version}" and r.test == "${test}" and r.duration == "${duration}" and r.users == "${users}")
  |> keep(columns: ["_value","_time","_field"])
  |> pivot(rowKey:["_time"], columnKey: ["_field"], valueColumn: "_value")
  |>  reduce(fn: (r, accumulator) => (
        {count: r.count + accumulator.count, 
         countError: r.countError + accumulator.countError
        }
        ), 
        identity: {count: 0.0, countError: 0.0})
    |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with _value: (r.count / (r.countError + r.count)) }))
    |> keep(columns: ["_value"])

from(bucket: v.defaultBucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "statistics")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "avg"  and r.application == "${app}" and r.env == "${env}" and r.version == "${version}" and r.test == "${test}" and r.duration == "${duration}" and r.users == "${users}")
  |> keep(columns: ["_field","_time","_value"])
  |> mean()

from(bucket: v.defaultBucket)
